in any way.

178
00:07:58,033 --> 00:08:00,033
Oh, okay.

179
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:05,400
If you want to speed up the
process of us going to America,

180
00:08:05,533 --> 00:08:07,067
then marry Gerald.

181
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:10,033
What?

182
00:08:15,433 --> 00:08:17,333
Marry Gerald.

183
00:08:17,467 --> 00:08:18,833
What?

184
00:08:18,967 --> 00:08:20,867
Marry him.

185
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:27,467
Because it's easier if one of us
marries a US citizen.

186
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:30,967
So we can fly right away, right?

187
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:33,400
What? Gina? Come on.

188
00:08:33,533 --> 00:08:35,233
Hey, that's enough, okay?

189
00:08:35,367 --> 00:08:36,433
You've had too much to drink.

190
00:08:36,567 --> 00:08:37,633
- No.
- You're saying a lot.

191
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:38,533
Gerald, wait a minute!

192
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:39,533
Listen!

193
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:42,067
Listen. You two, listen!

194
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,700
You two can get married.

195
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:49,400
If you get married,
you can get divorced.

196
00:08:49,533 --> 00:08:52,633
That's what an acquaintance
of my acquaintance did

197
00:08:52,767 --> 00:08:54,767
at the parlor.

198
00:08:54,933 --> 00:08:56,533
That's possible.

199
00:08:56,667 --> 00:09:01,300
Come on, you said you would
help us, right?

200
00:09:01,433 --> 00:09:02,067
Betsy...

201
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,067
that's enough.

202
00:09:07,233 --> 00:09:08,167
Don't be like that, come on.

203
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:12,000
What, Gina?

204
00:09:12,133 --> 00:09:15,033
Betsy...

205
00:09:15,167 --> 00:09:18,400
what you're asking of me
is too hard.

206
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:19,900
With Gerald?

207
00:09:21,767 --> 00:09:24,367
Don't you like him?

208
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,167
That's not a problem.

209
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:29,300
You had a crush
on Gerald before, right?

210
00:09:29,467 --> 00:09:30,533
Betsy!

211
00:09:30,667 --> 00:09:32,467
Come on.

212
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,667
That's enough.

213
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:34,233
That's enough.

214
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:44,000
- What's happening to you?
- Betsy, are you okay?

215
00:09:44,133 --> 00:09:46,100
Come on. Gina,
I'll take care of her.

216
00:09:46,233 --> 00:09:47,167
She's drunk.

217
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:49,067
Go home, okay?

218
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:51,067
What?

219
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,600
Water?

220
00:09:52,733 --> 00:09:53,733
What do you want?

221
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:54,767
Come on.

222
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,300
Come on. Come on.

223
00:09:56,433 --> 00:09:57,167
Gina, what?

224
00:09:57,300 --> 00:09:58,733
Think about it, okay?

225
00:09:58,867 --> 00:09:59,667
Come on. Come on.

226
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:02,900
Come on, come on.

227
00:10:03,033 --> 00:10:03,967
Let's go there.

228
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:04,667
Slowly.

229
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:11,400
<i> That Gina is annoying.</i>

230
00:10:11,533 --> 00:10:13,833
It's just a fake wedding
and yet she's so fuzzy!

231
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,633
Betsy...

232
00:10:19,167 --> 00:10:22,267
Are you sure
of what you said earlier?

233
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,033
Yes.

234
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:26,800
I'm just drunk
but my mind is clear.

235
00:10:26,933 --> 00:10:30,733
You'll save more and you'll get
to the US faster

236
00:10:30,867 --> 00:10:32,433
if you marry Gina.

237
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:37,567
Just compare it from if you take
care of the paperwork,

238
00:10:37,733 --> 00:10:39,867
you'll pay the agency.

239
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:43,433
And you need a place
to stay there.

240
00:10:43,567 --> 00:10:45,200
Betsy.

241
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:47,667
Take that out of your mind.

242
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,867
No one will marry someone else.

243
00:10:52,633 --> 00:10:59,200
Gerald, we need a sure plan
for you to become a US citizen.

244
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:01,733
So, is that the sure plan
you're thinking of?

245
00:11:01,867 --> 00:11:04,167
For me to marry Gina?

246
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:06,333
Betsy, please!

247
00:11:06,467 --> 00:11:07,800
Do you think I'll agree?

248
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:10,367
Especially Gina,
would she agree?

249
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:12,633
Well, I'm just
thinking of a way

250
00:11:12,767 --> 00:11:14,933
because I'm already
rotting here.

251
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:27,700
Hello, Chiqui.

252
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:30,900
When's the party
with Ms. Cita again?

253
00:11:31,033 --> 00:11:32,700
The one you mentioned
earlier in the parlor.

254
00:11:34,633 --> 00:11:35,667
<i> There, okay?</i>

255
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,667
I'll give you
my other groceries.

256
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:42,900
