268
00:12:06,033 --> 00:12:07,233
Hope everyone!

269
00:12:12,767 --> 00:12:14,433
You know, Betsy,

270
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,200
that's why
I asked you to come here,

271
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:19,133
because it looks like Andrew
will like you.

272
00:12:19,267 --> 00:12:22,900
Ronalyn's husband's
coworker in Texas.

273
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,700
He's looking for a Filipina
to marry

274
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:26,633
and then he'll bring her back
to America.

275
00:12:26,767 --> 00:12:29,567
Let me introduce you, okay?

276
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:30,800
What? Do you want?

277
00:12:30,933 --> 00:12:32,367
Do you want to see the picture?

278
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:34,267
- Okay. Let me see.
- This.

279
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:36,233
Look.

280
00:12:36,367 --> 00:12:37,533
Handsome.

281
00:12:37,667 --> 00:12:40,133
He was handsome
when he was younger.

282
00:12:40,267 --> 00:12:41,400
He's divorced already.

283
00:12:41,533 --> 00:12:42,733
What now? Do you want it?

284
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:45,167
I'll call him.

285
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,000
- That will do.
- Okay.

286
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:47,167
Yes, okay.

287
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:48,667
I'll call him, okay?

288
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:50,533
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

289
00:12:50,667 --> 00:12:51,433
Okay. Wait.

290
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,433
<i> Hello?</i>

291
00:12:59,567 --> 00:13:00,800
<i> Hello, Andrew.</i>

292
00:13:00,933 --> 00:13:02,133
<i> Hi!</i>

293
00:13:02,267 --> 00:13:03,467
<i> How are you?</i>

294
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:08,967
I want you to meet
my beautiful neighbor.

295
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:10,300
Her name is Betsy.

296
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,467
<i> She's beautiful.</i>

297
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:15,867
<i> She's my neighbor.</i>

298
00:13:16,467 --> 00:13:18,733
Betsy is so shameless,
isn't she?

299
00:13:19,533 --> 00:13:23,667
She really offered
her own boyfriend to you

300
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:25,633
for their American dream.

301
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:29,833
You know, I don't think she's
serious about that, Auntie.

302
00:13:29,967 --> 00:13:31,767
She'll think of something else.

303
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:35,400
My aunt will go first.

304
00:13:35,533 --> 00:13:37,533
Wait, I'll make
an additional order.

305
00:13:37,667 --> 00:13:39,567
This seems to be more delicious.

306
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:45,133
One leche flan and then...

307
00:13:45,267 --> 00:13:46,600
- this iced tea.
- Betsy?

308
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:47,400
<i> Wow!</i>

309
00:13:47,533 --> 00:13:48,633
<i> Here you are. I'm here.</i>

310
00:13:48,767 --> 00:13:49,467
<i> What took you so long?</i>

311
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,467
Sorry.

312
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,500
<i> I'm here now.</i>

313
00:13:51,633 --> 00:13:52,333
<i> It's about time.</i>

314
00:13:52,467 --> 00:13:54,333
<i> Let's go. Let's order.</i>

315
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,200
<i> Oh, sure.</i>

316
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:56,633
<i>Get the menu and then we order.</i>

317
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:08,700
Betsy, what are you doing?

318
00:14:14,233 --> 00:14:15,567
Does Gerald know this?

319
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:19,067
<i>What are you and Betsy's plans?</i>

320
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,933
I'll keep working.

321
00:14:21,067 --> 00:14:22,800
Maybe I'll review
for the NCLEX first.

322
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:24,133
Oh, wait.

323
00:14:24,267 --> 00:14:27,100
You will go first and then
Betsy will be left here?

324
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:30,833
Oh my, she'll make a scene here.

325
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,800
Well, we don't have a choice.

326
00:14:32,933 --> 00:14:35,233
Besides, she'll understand.

327
00:14:35,367 --> 00:14:36,833
Partner, my point is,

328
00:14:36,967 --> 00:14:39,100
all I know is that long distance
relationships are hard.

329
00:14:39,233 --> 00:14:41,967
And in the States,
there are many beautiful women.

330
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:43,300
The white ones
are the most beautiful.

331
00:14:43,433 --> 00:14:44,933
- You will be trapped!
- Stop with your nonsense!

332
00:14:45,067 --> 00:14:45,767
Hey, hook me up with them.

333
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:46,667
I like tall ones.

334
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,100
This, this is my favorite.

335
00:14:49,233 --> 00:14:50,433
Especially the blue one.

336
00:14:54,033 --> 00:14:56,533
Good morning.

337
00:14:56,667 --> 00:14:58,500
Betsy's not here.

338
00:14:58,633 --> 00:15:00,367
Someone picked her up earlier.

339
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,800
Who's Gerald?

340
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:03,900
That's her boyfriend.

341
00:15:04,033 --> 00:15:05,467
No way. I'm her boyfriend.

342
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:06,533
No, no, no.

343
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:07,633
She's lying.

344
00:15:07,767 --> 00:15:08,633
- Don't believe her.
- Come on.

345
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:12,333
You wait here, okay?

346
00:15:12,467 --> 00:15:15,033
Come here.

347
00:15:15,167 --> 00:15:17,267
Why are you interfering?

348
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,200
What are you doing?

349
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:22,067
Gerald is making sacrifices
for the two of you,

350
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:25,033
and you're dating someone else?

351
00:15:25,167 --> 00:15:26,667
Leave it alone.

352
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,867
Gerald will also know
about my plan.

353
00:15:31,033 --> 00:15:32,867
Who picked her up?
Did you see them?

354
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:36,733
No.

355
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:38,000
That...

356
00:15:53,933 --> 00:15:56,200
What are you talking about?

357
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:58,467
I'm going to flirt
with that American guy.

358
00:15:58,600 --> 00:15:59,533
My God, Betsy.

359
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:01,467
And then I'll marry him!

360
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:04,233
He'll be my ticket
and Gerald's to America!

361
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,300
Don't ruin this.

362
00:16:07,433 --> 00:16:11,067
After all, you don't want
to marry him, right?

363
00:16:11,233 --> 00:16:13,933
You really want me
to marry Gerald for you?

364
00:16:14,067 --> 00:16:15,500
That's going to take years
of my life

365
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:19,067
to be married to someone
who is just using me for you!

366
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:23,767
Hey, you talk as if I haven't
done anything good for you!

367
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:27,567
Not only did Gerald save
your life, but me too.

368
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:31,167
Wow. Now is the time to pay
for debt of gratitude.

369
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:33,000
Yes. And it's due date already!

370
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:36,000
If it weren't for me,

371
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:39,067
you might be dead
and not in America.

372
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,367
But don't worry.

373
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,233
I won't force you.

374
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,400
And I won't kneel
in front of you

375
00:16:44,533 --> 00:16:47,333
to try to get you to help us.

376
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:50,067
So please, excuse me,
I still have a date.

377
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,333
Betsy, wait.

378
00:16:51,467 --> 00:16:54,700
Not all foreigners looking
for Filipinas are decent.

379
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:57,633
Can you stop being
so desperate?

380
00:16:57,767 --> 00:16:59,833
It's you who should stop.

381
00:16:59,967 --> 00:17:01,567
Stop giving me
that fake concern of yours

382
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:05,000
because that won't do anything
to improve my life.

383
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:08,200
- Betsy.
- Get out of here.

384
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:09,200
What's going on?

385
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,433
Baby Andrew, are you okay?

386
00:17:10,567 --> 00:17:11,400
- Yeah.
- Please sit down.

387
00:17:11,533 --> 00:17:12,300
- Are you sure?
- Everything is okay.

388
00:17:12,433 --> 00:17:13,633
- Yes.
- Okay.

389
00:17:13,767 --> 00:17:14,867
Sit down.

390
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:19,333
Sorry, Ma'am.

391
00:17:19,467 --> 00:17:20,267
- There!
- No, it's okay.

392
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,833
I'll just get a towel.

393
00:17:21,967 --> 00:17:22,800
No, it's okay.

394
00:17:22,933 --> 00:17:24,400
That's good for you.

395
00:17:24,533 --> 00:17:25,933
You're blocking the way.

396
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,833
What? Are you going to fight?

397
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:30,867
Are you going to say
something else?

398
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,700
I'm desperate, remember?

399
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:33,867
So don't pick on me.

400
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,267
I'll hit you here.

401
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:39,200
Betsy, I've been your friend
for a long time.

402
00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:40,867
I'm just concerned for you.

403
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,633
If you're my friend,

404
00:17:42,767 --> 00:17:45,067
you should understand
why I'm doing this!

405
00:17:46,933 --> 00:17:49,433
The problem with you is
you don't know the reality

406
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,900
of Gerald and me.

407
00:17:52,033 --> 00:17:53,667
You're privileged!

408
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,300
You're rich,

409
00:17:55,433 --> 00:17:58,433
so you don't know
and it's none of your business.

410
00:17:58,567 --> 00:18:00,633
I'm ready to help you.

411
00:18:00,767 --> 00:18:02,967
But not in the way you want.

412
00:18:03,100 --> 00:18:04,833
Well, then you can't help!

413
00:18:04,967 --> 00:18:06,433
That's nothing!

414
00:18:06,567 --> 00:18:08,967
So please just leave here!

415
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:11,033
And just so you know,

416
00:18:11,167 --> 00:18:15,300
there are many desperate people
now who have already prospered!

417
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:23,133
<i> What is this all about?</i>

418
00:18:23,267 --> 00:18:24,367
<i> Can we eat now?</i>

419
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:30,233
Auntie, I'll just go
to the bathroom.

420
00:18:30,367 --> 00:18:31,233
Gina!

421
00:18:39,167 --> 00:18:42,067
Leave that girl alone.

422
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:43,500
There's nothing you can do

423
00:18:43,633 --> 00:18:46,933
if she wants to hook up
with someone.

424
00:18:47,067 --> 00:18:49,233
Gerald needs to know this.

425
00:18:55,967 --> 00:18:57,000
Gina.

426
00:18:57,133 --> 00:18:58,233
Gina!

427
00:18:58,367 --> 00:19:02,433
Betsy herself said,
don't meddle with them.

428
00:19:02,567 --> 00:19:04,033
That's their life.

429
00:19:04,167 --> 00:19:07,433
You'll only make things
worse if you report it.

430
00:19:07,567 --> 00:19:08,667
Don't try.

431
00:19:13,700 --> 00:19:14,967
Gerald is calling.

432
00:19:18,433 --> 00:19:19,533
Hello?

433
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:24,933
Gina, sorry I called.

434
00:19:25,067 --> 00:19:27,267
<i> I can't contact Betsy.</i>

435
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:28,600
Are you together?

436
00:19:28,767 --> 00:19:30,767
Maybe just call her again.

437
00:19:32,367 --> 00:19:33,967
Well, I thought you were
the one who picked her up

438
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:34,833
from her house.

439
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:37,233
Wait.

440
00:19:37,367 --> 00:19:39,467
Have you talked
since last night?

441
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:40,733
<i> Gerald, sorry.</i>

442
00:19:40,867 --> 00:19:42,633
But if you have an issue
with Betsy,

443
00:19:42,767 --> 00:19:44,100
that's yours alone.

444
00:19:44,233 --> 00:19:45,233
<i> I'm out of the picture.</i>

445
00:19:49,267 --> 00:19:50,133
So what?

446
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:52,233
Where's Betsy?

447
00:19:52,367 --> 00:19:54,333
I don't know.

448
00:19:54,467 --> 00:19:55,833
It seems Gina
doesn't know either.

449
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:03,467
Oh, sure, I do have.

450
00:20:03,633 --> 00:20:04,900
Let me check. Oh, here.

451
00:20:05,033 --> 00:20:06,333
No password will do, right?

452
00:20:06,467 --> 00:20:08,300
- Thank you, Sir.
- You're welcome.

453
00:20:10,967 --> 00:20:13,433
Andrew, can we leave now?

454
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:14,067
Sure.

455
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:14,833
Let's go now.

456
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:15,600
Let's make a move.

457
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:21,633
After you.

458
00:20:21,767 --> 00:20:22,467
Sir?

459
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:29,367
Sir!

460
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:37,700
Betsy, do you want
to introduce me

461
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:39,400
to your beautiful friend
over here?

462
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:45,100
She was just a friend
when I was in...

463
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:46,167
- Are you sure?
- in childhood.

464
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:47,800
Sure?

465
00:20:47,933 --> 00:20:49,300
- You don't have to know her.
- Okay.

466
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:50,200
Let's just go.

467
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:52,300
- All right. Let's go.
- Let's go.

468
00:20:52,433 --> 00:20:53,333
See you.

469
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:59,100
You know, let's go.

470
00:20:59,233 --> 00:21:01,967
And you might even get involved
with Betsy's foolishness.

471
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:03,033
Come on.

472
00:21:03,167 --> 00:21:04,633
Auntie, there's something
wrong with that guy.

473
00:21:04,767 --> 00:21:05,933
I'm restless.

474
00:21:06,067 --> 00:21:07,667
What?

475
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:09,833
I don't know, Auntie
but something's off.

476
00:21:11,467 --> 00:21:14,867
Ma'am, do you know that woman
and the foreigner with her?

477
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,900
The one you were
talking to earlier.

478
00:21:17,033 --> 00:21:17,400
Yeah.

479
00:21:17,533 --> 00:21:18,600
Yeah, I do. Why?

480
00:21:18,733 --> 00:21:20,900
The foreigner left
his passport behind.

481
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:22,467
Please give it to me.

482
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:23,367
Okay, I'll take care of it.

483
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:24,167
Okay.

484
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,567
Come on, Gina.

485
00:21:39,967 --> 00:21:40,533
Oh my God!

486
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:41,967
My suspicions are correct!

487
00:21:42,133 --> 00:21:43,600
That guy has a criminal record.

488
00:21:43,733 --> 00:21:44,433
I'll follow them, okay?

489
00:21:44,567 --> 00:21:45,933
- Betsy!
- Gina!

490
00:21:46,067 --> 00:21:47,467
Where are you going?

491
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:50,767
Thank you, Mister.

492
00:21:50,900 --> 00:21:51,733
Thank you so much.

493
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,400
Driver, get in. Come on.

494
00:21:55,533 --> 00:21:56,200
Let's go.

495
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:00,567
Okay.

496
00:22:00,700 --> 00:22:02,300
Here we go.

497
00:22:02,433 --> 00:22:04,233
All right.

498
00:22:04,367 --> 00:22:06,133
Let's go to a nice place.

499
00:22:06,267 --> 00:22:07,733
Where do we go now, Sir?

500
00:22:07,867 --> 00:22:09,133
Come on, let's go to the hotel.

501
00:22:09,267 --> 00:22:10,133
Did you get a nice hotel here?

502
00:22:10,267 --> 00:22:11,667
What do you think?
We go there and relax?

503
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:12,733
Chill out. What do you think?

504
00:22:12,867 --> 00:22:15,367
- Sure, sure. Okay.
- Okay. Perfect.

505
00:22:15,533 --> 00:22:16,567
Mister, hurry up!

506
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:17,633
Come on, let's go!

507
00:22:17,767 --> 00:22:18,700
No.

508
00:22:18,833 --> 00:22:19,433
- Mister!
- Betsy!

509
00:22:19,567 --> 00:22:20,967
Mister, let's go! Let's go!

510
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:21,867
- Betsy!
- Go, go, go, go!

511
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,033
- Don't go with him!
- What is this?

512
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:23,900
Mister, let's go!

513
00:22:24,033 --> 00:22:24,667
Let's go.

514
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:25,733
- Go!
- Mister, go ahead!

515
00:22:25,867 --> 00:22:26,700
Hey!

516
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:40,067
<i>We're sorry,
all circuits are busy.</i>

517
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:42,433
<i> Please try your call again.</i>

518
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,067
Why is her phone still off?

519
00:22:51,033 --> 00:22:51,833
Gina.

520
00:22:51,967 --> 00:22:53,600
Gerald, sorry I didn't
tell you earlier

521
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:55,000
but I know where Betsy is.

522
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:57,000
She went with the
foreigner earlier.

523
00:22:57,133 --> 00:22:57,900
Who is that?

524
00:22:58,033 --> 00:22:59,333
I don't know him either, Gerald.

525
00:22:59,467 --> 00:23:00,800
Why are they together?

526
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:02,233
I don't know either, Gerald.

527
00:23:02,367 --> 00:23:04,600
All I know is, the guy
she's with is a red flag.

528
00:23:04,733 --> 00:23:07,067
I'm following them now.

529
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:09,133
<i>Where are you?
I'll go to you now.</i>

530
00:23:09,267 --> 00:23:10,167
San Antonio Drive.

531
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:11,667
I'll text you, okay?

532
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:21,867
There it is.

533
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:22,867
Thank you so much.

534
00:23:23,033 --> 00:23:24,233
Have a great night. Bye.

535
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:31,433
What are we doing here, Andrew?

536
00:23:31,567 --> 00:23:33,600
Oh, well, what do you think
we're going to do here, Baby?

537
00:23:33,733 --> 00:23:34,867
You, naughty girl.

538
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:40,700
If we do it...

539
00:23:42,100 --> 00:23:44,533
do you promise
to bring me to America?

540
00:23:44,667 --> 00:23:46,533
Oh, yes. I'll marry you,
bring you to America,

541
00:23:46,667 --> 00:23:49,633
and do whatever you want to.

542
00:23:49,767 --> 00:23:51,467
Sounds promising.

543
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:53,733
Excuse me.

544
00:23:53,867 --> 00:23:55,667
Has Andre Ray Coomer
checked in here?

545
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:58,567
He's white with a Filipina.

546
00:23:58,700 --> 00:23:59,933
We'll just check, Ma'am.

547
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:05,767
Upon checking in, Ma'am,
they just checked in.

548
00:24:05,900 --> 00:24:07,733
Can I get the room number?

549
00:24:07,867 --> 00:24:11,133
Because he left his passport
with me.

550
00:24:11,267 --> 00:24:12,700
And I need to give it to him.

551
00:24:12,833 --> 00:24:14,867
I also need to talk
to my friend.

552
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:19,100
Ma'am, I'm sorry, but I can't
take you straight to their room.

553
00:24:19,233 --> 00:24:22,033
Is it okay, Ma'am,
if I call them to their room?

554
00:24:22,167 --> 00:24:23,500
Kindly wait here, Ma'am.

555
00:24:23,633 --> 00:24:24,167
Oh, okay.

556
00:24:30,133 --> 00:24:31,867
Gina, where is Betsy?

557
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,867
Gerald, I haven't talked
to her yet

558
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:39,567
but she checked in here with...

559
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:42,033
the foreigner she dated earlier.

560
00:24:42,167 --> 00:24:44,133
Sorry, I didn't tell you sooner.

561
00:24:44,267 --> 00:24:45,800
What are you talking about?

562
00:24:45,933 --> 00:24:48,200
Why would Betsy date foreigners?

563
00:24:48,333 --> 00:24:49,467
Ma'am.

564
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:50,833
Excuse me, Ma'am.

565
00:24:50,967 --> 00:24:51,800
Ma'am, I'm sorry,

566
00:24:51,933 --> 00:24:54,367
but Mr. Coomer's line
is still busy.

567
00:24:56,267 --> 00:24:59,000
Is there no other way for me
to talk to my friend?

568
00:24:59,133 --> 00:25:01,200
Her companion has
a criminal record.

569
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:03,933
Ma'am, I understand
but we are not allowed

570
00:25:04,100 --> 00:25:06,500
to give out information
about our guests.

571
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:11,867
Let's call the police.

572
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:13,533
What do we tell the police?

573
00:25:13,667 --> 00:25:16,633
That something might
happen to our friend?

574
00:25:16,767 --> 00:25:19,200
I'll talk to the
receptionist again.

575
00:25:19,333 --> 00:25:21,733
Miss Jackie, Mr. Coomer
left his credit card.

576
00:25:21,867 --> 00:25:23,733
Just send it to room 405.

577
00:25:23,867 --> 00:25:24,767
- Thank you.
- Okay.

578
00:25:35,867 --> 00:25:39,500
I want you right now,
right here.

579
00:25:39,633 --> 00:25:41,067
It's not your fault, Gina.

580
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:43,033
If I had pushed her harder,
Gerald,

581
00:25:43,167 --> 00:25:45,400
this wouldn't have
ended like this.

582
00:25:45,533 --> 00:25:46,467
I'm really sorry.

583
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:47,900
Let me die!

584
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:49,533
I don't want it anymore!
I don't want it anymore!

585
00:25:49,667 --> 00:25:51,667
I don't want it anymore!
I don't want to live!

586
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:55,467
For Betsy's sake, marry me.

587
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:58,400
Whatever you want in return,
just marry me.
